Until version 1.7:
    Sequences operate on bytes, not characters
    Optimize decoding: decode adjacent letters and write them at once
    Split term.c to screen.c/misc.c/parse.c/term.c
    Rewrap lines
        Allow disable rewrapping only for screen/part below cursor, while keep rewrapping scrollback
        Recalculate non-rectangular selection position on resize
        Do something with multi-line shell prompt eating history lines
        Make selection operate on physical lines?
            allows to get rid of term->view (and its recalculation on resize)
            allows to keep non-rectangular selections after resizing
    CSI ? 4 l / CSI ? 4 h -- DECSCLM
    CSI > Ps q -- XTVERSION -> DCS > | text ST
    Refactor config
        Split global and perinstance settings, reload reliably
        Allow geometry to be specified in characters
        Implement named values for options instead of numeric
    Print
        Printing with SGR
        More advanced printing method (command with pipe)
